### Key Findings

- **Inactive tabs need `border-b-2 border-transparent`** (not no border at all) — this keeps active/inactive tabs the same height and prevents layout shift when the active indicator appears. This is the standard pattern across Flowbite, Tailkits, and Material Design 3.
- **Header restructure needed in `GraphView.tsx`**: replace the current `absolute top-4 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2` centered search bar with a full-width top header (`absolute top-0 left-0 right-0`) containing tabs on the left and the search input on the right — matching the design file exactly.
- **Active state**: `text-primary font-semibold border-b-2 border-primary pb-1`; **Inactive state**: `text-on-surface-variant border-b-2 border-transparent hover:text-on-surface transition-colors`
- **Use `<button>` not `<a>`** for the tab triggers — they change state, not location. Add `role="tablist"` / `role="tab"` / `aria-selected` for accessibility.
- **Sidebar icon toggle can stay untouched** — the issue explicitly says it "can remain" for power-user access.

### Gaps

- MD3 recommends 48dp tab height — need to verify the new header bar visually fits without crowding the graph canvas

Sources:
- [Flowbite Tabs Documentation](https://flowbite.com/docs/components/tabs/)
- [Tailkits Active Tab Guide](https://tailkits.com/blog/tailwind-active-tab/)
- [Tabs – Material Design 3](https://m3.material.io/components/tabs/guidelines)
- [ARIA: tab role – MDN Web Docs](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Reference/Roles/tab_role)
- [Keyboard Accessible Tabs with React – DEV Community](https://dev.to/eevajonnapanula/keyboard-accessible-tabs-with-react-5ch4)
