## PR #709 Code Review — `feat: add List/Graph toggle tabs to GraphView header`

**Status**: Draft | 1 file changed | +88 / -78 | CI: pending

---

### Overview

This PR restructures `GraphView.tsx` to add a `h-12` header bar containing List/Graph navigation tabs, and relocates the floating search bar from an absolute-centered position to the header's right side. The outer container switches from a single `relative` div to a `flex flex-col` wrapper, with `containerRef` correctly reassigned to the inner graph div so ResizeObserver measures only the graph area. The popover offset adjusts from `top-16` to `top-4` to account for the header no longer being in its parent.

The restructure is correct and cleanly done.

---

### Code Quality & Correctness

**No issues found with the core logic.** A few smaller things to note:

- **Both `<button>` elements are missing `type="button"`** (`GraphView.tsx:280,285`). Without it they default to `type="submit"` and would submit any ancestor form. This component is unlikely to live inside a `<form>`, but it's a defensive habit worth keeping.

- **The Graph tab button has no `onClick`** — correct, since you're already on the graph view. No action needed; just noting it's intentional.

- **Search input width narrowed from `w-72` (288px) to `w-64` (256px)** — a minor functional change. Deliberate to fit in the header, but worth calling out since it slightly constrains query length visibility.

- **`setMainView` selector** (`GraphView.tsx:93`) follows the existing store pattern correctly. No issue.

---

### Accessibility Gap

The active tab has no ARIA indicator:

```tsx
<button className="text-on-surface font-semibold border-b-2 border-primary pb-1">
  Graph
</button>
```

Should be:

```tsx
<button aria-current="page" className="...">Graph</button>
```

Without this, screen readers cannot distinguish the active tab from the inactive one.

---

### Minor Design Concern

The tab strip uses `<nav>` semantically correctly, but the two buttons lack a shared `role="tablist"` / `role="tab"` ARIA pattern. For a tab-style widget the ARIA tab pattern is preferred over `aria-current="page"` (which is for navigation links). Either is functional, but if this UI grows to more tabs, the tab role will be cleaner.

---

### Summary

| Area | Assessment |
|------|-----------|
| Correctness | ✅ Sound — flex layout, ref reassignment, popover offset all correct |
| Conventions | ✅ Follows design-system tokens (`bg-surface-container-low`, `text-on-surface-variant`, etc.) |
| Test coverage | ✅ No logic changes; 320 existing tests pass |
| Security | ✅ No concerns |
| Accessibility | ⚠️ Missing `aria-current="page"` (or ARIA tab roles) on active tab |
